# Non-CET Admission Engine — Frontend Behavior Model

> **Scope**: School, Junior College, Coaching  
> **Source of truth**: Backend services in `server/src/services/admissions/`  
> **This document defines LOGIC ONLY** — no UI, no routes, no JSX, no backend code.

---

## 1. Authentication Flow Logic

### 1.1 Phone OTP Flow (Primary for Non-CET)

The backend's `strategy-selector.js` assigns `auth_method: "phone_otp"` to school, coaching, and junior_college org types.

```
STEP 1: IDENTIFIER INPUT
  ├─ User enters 10-digit Indian mobile number
  ├─ Frontend validates: /^[6-9]\d{9}$/ (Indian mobile regex)
  ├─ If invalid → show inline error, block submission
  └─ If valid → proceed to OTP request

STEP 2: OTP REQUEST
  ├─ Call Firebase Auth signInWithPhoneNumber()
  ├─ Firebase handles SMS delivery + reCAPTCHA
  ├─ On success → store confirmationResult in memory (NOT localStorage)
  ├─ Start 60-second cooldown timer for resend
  ├─ On failure:
  │   ├─ "too-many-requests" → show "Too many attempts. Try after 5 minutes."
  │   ├─ "invalid-phone-number" → show "Invalid phone number format."
  │   └─ network error → show "Network error. Check your connection."
  └─ Max 3 OTP requests per session

STEP 3: OTP VERIFICATION
  ├─ User enters 6-digit OTP
  ├─ Call confirmationResult.confirm(otp)
  ├─ On success → get Firebase ID token
  ├─ Send ID token to POST /api/admission/verify-phone
  │   ├─ Backend returns { token, application_id, status }
  │   ├─ Store `token` in localStorage as "admission_token"
  │   └─ If application_id exists → RESUME SESSION (existing application)
  │   └─ If no application_id → NEW APPLICATION (draft will be created on first save)
  ├─ On OTP failure:
  │   ├─ "invalid-verification-code" → show "Invalid OTP. Please check and retry."
  │   ├─ Decrement remaining attempts (max 3)
  │   └─ After 3 failures → force new OTP request
  └─ On token verification failure (backend 401) → clear state, restart flow

STEP 4: SESSION RESTORE
  ├─ On page load, check localStorage for "admission_token"
  ├─ If found → call GET /api/admission/candidate/me
  │   ├─ 200 → restore full application state, skip auth
  │   ├─ 401 → token expired, clear localStorage, show auth screen
  │   └─ 500 → show generic error, allow retry
  └─ Session is stateless (JWT), no server-side session to expire
```

### 1.2 Email OTP Flow (Fallback)

```
STEP 1: Email input → validate email format
STEP 2: POST /api/admission/send-email-otp → backend sends OTP via Brevo
STEP 3: User enters OTP → POST /api/admission/verify-email-otp
STEP 4: Same token storage + session restore as phone flow
```

### 1.3 Mode Selection Logic

```
if (form_schema.auth_method === "cet_en_otp") → CET flow (NOT covered here)
if (form_schema.auth_method === "phone_otp") → Phone OTP (default for Non-CET)
  └─ User can toggle to Email OTP via UI switch
```

